26/04/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Enhancing bilateral economic ties is the focus of Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov's two-day visit to Serbia-Montenegro, which began Tuesday (25 April).
During meetings with Serbia-Montenegro counterpart Svetozar Marovic, Montenegrin President Filip Vujanovic and Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica, Parvanov stressed that bilateral political relations are excellent, but added that more could be done concerning economic and trade co-operation.
He also called for improving the situation of the Bulgarian minority in Serbia.
Wednesday, Parvanov meets with Serbian counterpart Boris Tadic in Dimitrovgrad.
(RTS - 26/04/06;
BNR, BTA - 25/04/06)
